value.0: This heavy-set fellow was known around Swamprise as the man who kept the Howling Wolf tavern running.

*All fighters responsible for their own healing, if you can't heal yourself, bring someone who can.

*Fights end when one man surrenders or is unconscious.

*Wagers permitted, but don't place bets you can't pay.  We don't need unsolicited fights in the balcony.

*No Weapons, I catch you with a knife in your trousers and you'll be thrown out and refused future service.  This also means no gauntlets, rings, or boots of any kind are to be worn by fighters.  If caught, the items will be confiscated and you will be thrown out.

*I don't care if you get hit below the belt, real men can handle it.

*Fight fair, or near enough to avoid raising suspicion.
